metadata.name: The Climb #119
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, itâ€™s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

â€œThe Climbâ€ is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.

metadata.name: Flimsy #5
metadata.description:
This started as an abstract project but the output gradually came to resemble some creatures of the sea like jellyfish and sea slugs. I decided this time to go with the flow and added spines and eye spots to make them look a bit more organic.

Initially this will be a free mint as a reward to the holders of my existing projects. After a day or so the reserves will be removed and the remainder will be available to anyone for a small amount of tezos.

Primary Features:
Layout - Open 40%, Closed 40%, U-Shaped 15%, Radial 5%
Background - Spots 50%, Lines 50%
Spines - true 25%, false 75%
EyeSpots - true 25%, false 75%
Ridges - true 25%, false 75%
Marking - Bands 50%, Stripes 50%

Copyright 2022 Jeff Clark

metadata.name: Starmap - AI Study I #237
metadata.description:
Starmap brings you to different sectors of the generative art galaxy. A first of its kind generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow, which involves writing text prompts that get translated into javascript code. This project was created with English words and human imagination, but the programming of the piece is all AI.

The code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing some Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #1 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

metadata.name: Beautiful M1nds #60
metadata.description:
This project is dedicated to the beautiful minds of the last centuries. I am talking about philosophy, math, science, physics, everything related to human knowledge.

I chosen 6 illustrious thinkers: Karl Marx, Stephen Hawking, Albert Einstein, Nikola Tesla, Sigmund Freud and Alan Turing. Each one of them made the world to step forward on different perspectives.

The algorithm is creating the famous iconic shapes of the beautiful minds using only letters, and the letters are just taken from their own books:
Karl Marx - Das Kapital
Sigmund Freud - The Interpretation of Dreams
Stephen Hawking - Particle Creation by Black Holes
Nikola Tesla - The Inventions Researches and Writings
Albert Einstein - Relativity
Alan Turing - Computing Machinery and Intelligence

There are 3 features:
The Font
The Size of the Font
The Author

The smaller is the font size, the more accurate becomes the image.
This is a tribute to human knowledge but also to Visual Poetry Art or Data Poetry and phenomenal artists like Jiri Kolar.
